                "title": "Maternity Leave",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Employees are entitled to 126 calendar days of paid leave. Social security will pay 100% of the employee's average salary from the previous 3 months during this period (Capped at GEL 1,000 per month)"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "The employee can extend leave additional 17 calendar days at 100% pay capped at GEL 1,000."
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Paternity Leave",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "There is no paternity leave by law in Georgia. Fathers can use parental leave or any of the mother's unused maternity leave."
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Parental Leave",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "Employees are entitled to 604 calendar days of parental leave. Both parents can decide how to distribute the time off. Social Security will pay 100% of the employees average salary from the previous 3 months during this period, capped at GEL 1,000 per month. Payment is only for the first 200 days after this period, it will be unpaid leave."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "data": "In addition, employees are also entitled to 12 weeks of unpaid parental leave per year until the child is 5 years of age."
                    }
                ]
            },
